Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper focuses on text mining historical local gazetteers to expand the contents of the China Biographical Database. This involves using language models to extract biographical information from the text. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper discusses the use of text mining techniques to extract relevant information from historical texts. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries): The paper deals with the expansion of a biographical database using historical local gazetteers, which are a type of digital library. 
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper discusses the expansion of a biographical database and the use of text mining techniques to extract information from historical texts. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses language models and text mining techniques to extract biographical information from historical texts, which falls under the umbrella of AI research.
